article.headline: E. Michigan 57, Cent. Michigan 56
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- Antonio Green had only three free throw attempts but made them all with 13 seconds left, giving Eastern Michigan a 57-56 win over Mid-American rival Central Michigan on Saturday night. Marcus Van scored a game-high 20 points in a losing effort for Central Michigan (9-18, 5-9 Mid-American). Zane Gay and Brandon Bowdry led Eastern Michigan (6-23, 4-10) with 12 points each, while Justin Dobbins added 11. Green finished with five points. Antonio Weary had 11 points for Central Michigan. Central Michigan led 30-28 at halftime and for the game outscored the Eagles 30-18 in the paint. But Eastern Michigan's bench outpaced the Chippewas 19-13 during a close game that featured nine ties and 15 lead changes.
